<title>Groovy</title>
<description>

<p>
Groovy is an agile, dynamic programming language that compiles source files
directly to java bytecode.  Groovy has a syntax similar to Java and includes
features found in Python, Ruby, and Smalltalk.  
</p>

See also:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://groovy.codehaus.org/">Groovy homepage</a>
</li><li><a href="http://dist.codehaus.org/groovy/distributions/">Groovy download</a>
</li><li><a href="http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=241">JSR 241: The Groovy Programming Language</a>
</li></ul>
</description>
